doc.after: During the Second World War, Royal Artillery military fortifications were established at the beach end of the reserve, including two 6-inch (15.24Â cm) guns, five buildings, two pillboxes, a minefield,[2] and concrete anti-tank blocks. A spigot mortar emplacement and an Allan Williams Turret machine gun emplacement were sited closer to the village. One of the pillboxes and remains of the beach gun emplacements were still surviving as of 2012.[19]
